#ad Pineapple Chipotle BBQ Burger! Made in partnership with @bubbaburger ! Grilled pineapple just makes sense on a burger. I love the flavors of pineapple with jalapeno, so I figured using smoked jalapenos - AKA Chipotle, would take the flavor combo one step further! BUBBA Burgers are flash frozen to lock in all that amazing flavor, and the Sweet Onion - my favorite flavor - was a great match for these toppings.

Chicken Bacon Ranch Burgers w/ @bubbaburger 

Ingredients:

BUBBA Chicken Burgers - 2lb
Onion - 2
Bacon - 1lb
Salt Pepper Garlic Blend
Pepperjack Cheese
Kaiser Rolls

Jalapeño Ranch:
Mayo - 1/2c
Sour Cream - 1/2c
Buttermilk - 1/4c
Jalapeño - 2 (deseeded)
Honey - 1tbsp
Ranch Seasoning - 1tbsp 

Directions:

1. Thinly slice two onions and add to a bowl. 
2. Combine the mayo, sour cream and buttermilk. Add the jalapeño, honey and ranch seasoning. Blend until smooth and give it a taste. 
3. Head out to your griddle and fire it up. Add the bacon, onions and chicken burgers to the grill. Season the first side of the burgers with your favorite seasoning blend. 
4. Cook the burgers for 5-8mins on one side and then flip. Season the other side and cook for another 5-8mins before covering with a slice of cheese. Check the internal temp making sure it’s over 165 and then remove. 
5. Cook the bacon until crispy and then push the onions over to bacon grease before removing. Then add the Kaiser rolls to toast for a few mins. 
6. Assemble the burgers! Add some of your jalapeño ranch and then the burger topped with bacon and onions. I served the burgers with some Mac salad. Enjoy!
